Kitaca (キタカ, Kitaka) is a rechargeable contactless smart card ticketing system for public transport in Sapporo, Japan.
Its name means "the card of north (北, kita)", while 北 is also the first character of Hokkaidō (北海道, Hokkaidō).
The service with SAPICA, a smart card system to be introduced by Sapporo City Transportation Bureau from January 2009, was also considered.
